name: Rattus norvegicus Adipose
procedure: 500mg of adipose tissue was placed in a 7 mL tube containting 2.8mm ceramic beads and 3 mL of water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Bos taurus amniotic membrane
procedure: 500mg of amniotic membrane was placed in a 7 mL tube containing 2.4mm metal beads, 2 x 6.5mm ceramic beads and 3 mL of PBS.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 f or 8 cycles of 30 seconds with 1 minute dwells on ice.
tag: Bead Ruptor 24, cow, amniotic membrane, protein, growth factors

name: Rattus norvegicus Brain
procedure: 30mg of brain was placed in a 2 mL tube containing 2.8mm ceramic beads and  750 _l Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 45 seconds

name: Rattus norvegicus Brain
procedure: 70mg of brain was placed in a 2 mL tube containing 1.4mm ceramic beads and  500 uL TBS.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4.85 m/s for 20 seconds

name: Oncorhynchus mykiss bone
procedure: 2 g of trout heads was placed in a 50 mL tube containing 2.8mm ceramic beads and 20 ml of 0.5% pepsin-HCL.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4.7 m/s for 3 cycles of 30 seconds with 2 minute dwells.

name: Rattus norvegicus colon
procedure: 3.6 g of rat colon was placed in a 30 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 10 mL of water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 3 cycles of 30 seconds with 1.5 minute dwells.

name: Drosophila melanogaster (whole)
procedure: 30-50mg of whole fruit flies were placed in a 2 mL tube 1.4mm ceramic beads and 1 mL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Anser anser domesticus Feather
procedure: 1 goose feather (100mg) was cut up and placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6.6 m/s for 5  cycles of 30 seconds with 3 minute dwells.

name: Anser anser domesticus Feather
procedure: 1 goose feather (100mg) was cut up and placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 12 on HIGH for 5  cycles of 30 seconds with 3 minute dwells.

name: Rattus norvegicus Femur
procedure: 200mg of rat femur was placed in a 7 mL with 2.4mm metal beads and 2 x 6.5mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 12 on HIGH for 2 cycles of 1 min with a 1 minute dwell on ice

name: Rattus norvegicus Heart
procedure: 50mg of rat heart was placed in a 2 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 1 mL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 12 on HIGH for 1 minute.

name: Rattus norvegicus Heart
procedure: 30mg of rat heart was placed in a 2 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 750 μl Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 2 cycles of 45 seconds with a 30 second dwell.

name: Rattus norvegicus liver
procedure: 30mg of rat liver was placed in a 2 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 750 μl Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 45 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Liver
procedure: 70mg of rat liver was placed in a 2 mL with 1.4mm ceramic beads and 500 μl TBS.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.3 m/s for 20 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Liver
procedure: 5 g of rat liver was placed in a 30 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 15 mL water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 2 cycles of 45 seconds.
tag: Bead Ruptor 24, rat, liver, small molucules

name: Rattus norvegicus Liver
procedure: 3 g of rat liver was placed in a 15 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 4 ml water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.8 m/s for 45 seconds.

name: Gallus gallus domesticus Liver
procedure: 2 g of rat liver was placed in a 15 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 3 ml water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6.45 m/s for 3 cycles of 30 seconds with dwells of 1 minute.
tag: Bead Ruptor 24, chicken, liver, small molecules

name: Gallus gallus domesticus Liver
procedure: 5 g of chiken liver was placed in a 30 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 10 ml water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 2 cycles of 45 seconds.
tag: Bead Ruptor 24, chiken, liver, small molucules

name: Gallus gallus domesticus Liver
procedure: 200mg of chiken liver was placed in a 7 mL with 2.8mm ceramic beads and  1.8mL 50:50 Methanol:H2O.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.3 m/s for 30 seconds.
tag: Bead Ruptor 24, chiken, liver, small molucules, pesticides, drugs

name: Rattus norvegicus Lung
procedure: 68mg of rat lung was placed in a 2 mL with 1.4mm ceramic beads and 500 μl TBS.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.5 m/s for 20 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Muscle
procedure: 55mg of rat muscle was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.4mm metal beads and 750 uL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 12 on HIGH for 45 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Muscle
procedure: 30mg of rat muscle was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 750 uL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 45 seconds.

name: Canis familiaris Placenta
procedure: 1 g of dog placenta was place in a 7 mL tube containing 2.8mm ceramic beads and 2 mL water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Artibeus phaeotis Skin
procedure: 25 - 100mg of bat skin containing fur was placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6.8m/s for 30 seconds.  3 mL of TCA was added to the tube and the sample was processed again at 6.8m/s for 3 cycles of 30 seconds

name: Sus domesticus Skin
procedure: 200mg of pig skin was placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramics and 2 mL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 6 m/s for 3 cycles of 30 seconds with 3 minute dwells on ice.

name: Rattus norvegicus Small Intestine
procedure: 30mg of rat small intestine was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 200 uL of lysis buffer from a DNA extraction kit.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 10 seconds.

name: Allocosa apora (whole)
procedure: 1 wolf spider (240mg) was placed in a 7 mL tube with 1.4mm ceramic beads and 2 mL Tris.  Sample was process on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Spleen
procedure: 60mg of rat spleen was placed in a 2 mL tube with 1.4mm ceramic beads and 500 uL TBS.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4.85 m/s for 20 seconds.

name: Rattus norvegicus Trachea
procedure: A 2-3mm2 (3-10mg) piece of rat trachea was placed in a 0.5 mL tube with 1.4mm ceramic beads and 250 uL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 2 cycles of 60 seconds

name: Tenebrio molitor
procedure: 30mg of a beetle was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 350 uL lysis buffer from a DNA extraction kit.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 4 for 30 seconds.

name: Solanum lycopersicum var. cerasiform Seeds
procedure: 20mg of cherry tomato seeds were placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.5 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Capsicum chinens Seeds
procedure: 20mg of chili pepper seeds  were placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.5 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Trifolium repens Leaves
procedure: 200mg of clover leaves was placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 1 mL Tris.  Sample was processed on a Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.65 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Humulus lupulus Flower
procedure: 100mg of hops were added to a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 3 mL water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 12 on HIGH for 30 seconds.

name: Lactuca sativa Seeds
procedure: 11mg of lettuce seeds were placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 500 uL water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Lactuca sativa Seeds
procedure: 11mg of lettuce seeds were placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 500 uL water.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 4 at speed 5 for 30 seconds.

name: Humulus lupulus Flower
procedure: 1.5 g of hops was placed in a 50 mL tube with five 6.5mm ceramic beads.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4 m/s for 5 cycles of 30 seconds with 30 second dwells.

name: Pisum sativum Seeds
procedure: 2 g of peas were placed in a 50 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 20 mL Tris. Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Pisum sativum Seeds
procedure: 2 g of peas were placed in a 30 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 20 mL Tris. Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Abelmoschus esculentus Pods
procedure: 180mg of okra was placed in a 7 mL tube with 2.8mm beads and 1.8 mL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Sorghum amplum Leaves
procedure: 100mg of sorghum was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 500 uL Tris.  Sample was processed at 5.5 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Spinacia oleracea Leaves
procedure: 2 g of spinach was placed in a 50 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 20 mL Tris. Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 60 seconds.

name: Spinacia oleracea Leaves
procedure: 2 g of spinach was placed in a 30 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 20 mL Tris. Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5 m/s for 60 seconds.

name: Saccharum officinarum Shoot
procedure: 100mg of sugarcane was placed in a 2 mL tube with 2.8mm ceramic beads and 500 uL Tris.  Sample was processed on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 5.5 m/s for 30 seconds

name: Triticum aestivum Kernel
procedure: 1 wheat berry (30-50mg) was placed in a 2 mL tube with one 6.5mm ceramic bead.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4.5 m/s for 30 seconds.

name: Pinus resinosa Chips
procedure: 100mg of a pine chip was placed in a 2 ml tube with one 6.5mm ceramic bead.  Sample was dry grinded on the Bead Ruptor 24 at 4.5 m/s for 3.5 minutes.
